<item>
            <title>[SHIRO-547] Use MessageDigest#isEqual() instead of Arrays#equals() for comparing digests</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SHIRO-547</link>
                <project id="12310950" key="SHIRO">Shiro</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While looking through shiro code I noticed that there are three places which compare byte[]s representing hashes using `Arrays#equals()`&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To avoid potential timing attacks these should be using `MessageDigest#isEqual()`, which at least starting with Java 6u17 uses a constant-time comparison.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not sure which Java version shiro targets, but it might make sense to either require Java 7, or to at least strongly suggest this in the documentation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Attached a patch against trunk, but please also consider fixing this in the 1.2 branch.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
